      Bio
      I am Assistant Professor (tenure track) of Quantitative Methods in the Faculty of Business Administration and Accounting at the Federal University of Rio de Janeiro - Brazil. My research interests are risk management, portfolio allocation, volatility forecasting, robust statistics, and statistical learning.
      I received the y-BIS Best Paper Award (2016), IASC-ERS Young Researchers Award (2018), and the Best paper Award in the Latin American Conference for Statistical Computing (2019).
      Before I joined the Federal University of Rio de Janeiro, I worked in Brazilian companies as a Data Science Specialist, Data Science Coordinator, and Data Scientist Consultant.
      Currently, my goal is to apply statistical learning techniques on Business, Economics and Finance as well as develop new volatility forecasting procedures in high-dimensional and high-frequency data.


